olive oil
½ tin sweetcorn
1 packet pulled chicken
1 packet garlic paste
1 avocado
1 lemon
2 tomato
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
8 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet sour cream
1 bag coriander
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Heat olive oil in frying pan over high heat. Drain sweetcorn (1/2 tin for 2P // 1 tin for 4P)
• Cook corn, chicken, garlic paste and spice blend, tossing, until heated through, 3-4 mins.

• Meanwhile, halve lemon and roughly chop tomato
• Cut avocado in half, scoop out flesh and roughly chop
• In a bowl, combine tomato, avocado and lemon juice. Season to taste
• In a separate bowl, combine slaw and chipotle sauce.

• Microwave tortillas for 10 second bursts, until warm
• Fill tortillas with chicken mixture, guacamole, slaw, sour cream, cheese
• Serve sprinkled with torn coriander.